      "content": "No, you absolutely cannot adjust your warfarin dose without a blood test because your body's clotting factors change unpredictably and too quickly to guess based on how you feel. Even if you feel fine, a sudden drop from 5mg to 2mg could cause dangerous clots, while an accidental over-reduction might lead to bleeding if your INR was already low. Please contact your doctor's urgent line or an emergency clinic immediately to discuss your situation; do not wait weeks to manage a medication that balances such a narrow margin.",
