      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear you about the blood tests and all that, but i also worry about the side effects of being on a high dose for too long. i've read online that a lot of people find they can maintain their levels with much lower doses once they've stabilized. if i'm being really careful and just doing a slow taper, like maybe 3mg for a bit first, wouldn't that be a much safer way to handle it than just jumping straight to 2mg? it feels more logical to ease into it if my body is stable.",
